│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The transformation moves a shufflevector that uses a select (on LHS) to       │
│ instead select between two shuffles (FoldOpIntoSelect). This is poison-unsafe │
│ because select with a poison condition yields poison for the entire result,   │
│ while the original "shuffle(select, ConstRHS, Mask)" can produce some defined │
│ lanes sourced from the RHS constant even if the LHS (select) is poison. Thus, │
│ the transform increases poison, as shown by Alive2.                           │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The first transformation is in visitShuffleVectorInst, where FoldOpIntoSelect │
│ is invoked for a shuffle whose RHS is a constant and LHS is a select with     │
│ integer condition:                                                            │
│ - Old: %shuf = shufflevector %sel, ConstRHS, Mask                             │
│ - New: %shuf = select %cmp, shufflevector %y, ConstRHS, Mask,                 │
│ ConstFoldedFalseArm                                                           │
│ Alive2 shows a counterexample with %cmp = poison where the source has defined │
│ elements (1,3) s coming from RHS, but the target is entirely poison because   │
│ the select consumes poison condition.                                         │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ FoldOpIntoSelect is being applied to a non-elementwise operation              │
│ (shufflevector with a mask that reads elements from both operands). The       │
│ comment in the code even warns "We cannot do this fold for elementwise select │
│ since ShuffleVector is not elementwise." Despite that, the fold is still      │
│ performed whenever RHS is constant and the LHS is a select with integer       │
│ condition. This is only safe if the shuffle mask references only the LHS      │
│ (i.e., it is effectively elementwise on LHS). If the mask references RHS      │
│ elements, the operation can "mask away" poison coming from LHS/select and     │
│ yield defined values. Moving select after the shuffle reintroduces poison     │
│ propagation from the condition and is thus incorrect.                         │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineVectorOps.cpp              │
│ - Lines: 2903-2911                                                            │
│ - Change: Guard the FoldOpIntoSelect for shuffle/select by ensuring it's only │
│ applied when the mask extracts exclusively from LHS. This keeps the           │
│ transformation within the elementwise-safe case. Use the existing helper      │
│ isShuffleExtractingFromLHS(SVI, Mask).                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ Original:                                                                     │
│   if (match(RHS, m_Constant())) {                                             │
│     if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(LHS)) {                               │
│       // We cannot do this fold for elementwise select since ShuffleVector is │
│       // not elementwise.                                                     │
│       if (SI->getCondition()->getType()->isIntegerTy()) {                     │
│         if (Instruction *I = FoldOpIntoSelect(SVI, SI))                       │
│           return I;                                                           │
│       }                                                                       │
│     }                                                                         │
│     ...                                                                       │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Replacement:                                                                  │
│   if (match(RHS, m_Constant())) {                                             │
│     if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(LHS)) {                               │
│       // We cannot do this fold for elementwise select since ShuffleVector is │
│       // not elementwise. Only safe if the shuffle extracts exclusively from  │
│ LHS.                                                                          │
│       if (SI->getCondition()->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&                     │
│           isShuffleExtractingFromLHS(SVI, Mask)) {                            │
│         if (Instruction *I = FoldOpIntoSelect(SVI, SI))                       │
│           return I;                                                           │
│       }                                                                       │
│     }                                                                         │
│     ...                                                                       │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ This change ensures we only perform the fold when Mask references LHS-only    │
│ elements (< LHSWidth), which makes the shuffle behave elementwise with        │
│ respect to LHS and avoids the poison-hiding behavior from RHS constants.      │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By restricting the FoldOpIntoSelect transformation for shuffle/select to      │
│ cases where the mask extracts solely from the LHS, we prevent incorrect       │
│ poison propagation changes. The fix preserves correctness in scenarios where  │
│ RHS contributes defined elements under poison conditions, as in the provided  │
│ reproducer, and maintains the intended optimization where it is safe.         │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
